      "side": 1,
      "message": "Looking at the way GitStore and AllRepos are used makes me wonder if a different organization might be simpler from the caller\u0027s perspective.  For example, if we renamed GitStore to GitRepoStore (since it deals with a single repo) and added a new, higher-level GitStore interface which has GetRepoInfos (which replaces AllRepos) and GitStoreForRepo methods, then the caller only has to do something like:\n\nbtStore, _ :\u003d gitstore.NewBigTableGitStore(ctx, *btProject, *btInstance, *btTable, ts)\nrepoInfo, _ :\u003d bts.GetRepoInfos()\n// TODO: Check whether *repoUrl exists in repoInfo\n// TODO: Check whether *branch exists in repoInfo[*repoUrl]\nstore :\u003d btStore.GitStoreForRepo(*repoUrl)\nstore.Get(...)",
